right?

255
00:37:53.980 --> 00:37:56.420
I need to get something
out of there tonight.

256
00:37:56.500 --> 00:38:00.660
- What do you need to get out?
- A shipment from a warehouse.

257
00:38:02.020 --> 00:38:05.660
- What is it?
- Jalapeno peppers.

258
00:38:29.340 --> 00:38:32.500
So. what do you say?

259
00:38:37.660 --> 00:38:41.780
Canned peppers stay good
for a long time. my friend.

260
00:38:45.460 --> 00:38:50.780
If I don't get it tonight the police
are going to open those cans.

261
00:38:50.860 --> 00:38:55.100
When they do they're going to find
five tons of cocaine.

262
00:38:59.380 --> 00:39:02.620
That's a lot of peppers.

263
00:39:14.020 --> 00:39:17.700
- The container is in warehouse 15.
- Thanks. - You're welcome.

264
00:39:17.820 --> 00:39:19.500
I have many friends in the port.

265
00:39:38.380 --> 00:39:41.660
Hurry up. we don't have all night!

266
00:39:41.700 --> 00:39:43.420
Come on!

267
00:39:54.980 --> 00:39:58.260
Hurry up with the second truck!

268
00:40:34.420 --> 00:40:35.500
Hey! What the hell!

269
00:40:38.820 --> 00:40:41.060
Fuck! Go. go!

270
00:40:58.020 --> 00:41:00.580
Go. go!

271
00:41:00.660 --> 00:41:02.340
Let's go!

272
00:41:07.900 --> 00:41:10.380
Fuck!

273
00:41:54.860 --> 00:41:57.540
Emma!

274
00:41:57.620 --> 00:42:02.340
- What?
- We gotta go. the police are coming.

275
00:42:12.660 --> 00:42:15.580
- Who the fuck is this guy?
- He's a friend. come on.

276
00:42:15.660 --> 00:42:18.860
- What's going on?
- I got our stuff out of the port.

277
00:42:18.940 --> 00:42:21.340
What?

278
00:42:21.420 --> 00:42:24.140
We're going to get it.
Come on. trust me!

279
00:42:24.540 --> 00:42:27.180
Where the fuck is our stuff. Chris?

280
00:42:30.060 --> 00:42:32.660
Fuck!

281
00:42:49.620 --> 00:42:53.340
Are all our cans here? Chris!

282
00:43:12.780 --> 00:43:16.620
This is their cut. 50 kilos.

283
00:43:19.380 --> 00:43:22.460
Are you out of your fucking mind?

284
00:43:22.540 --> 00:43:25.980
I am saving our shipment.

285
00:43:30.180 --> 00:43:31.660
You little shit!

286
00:43:31.780 --> 00:43:35.300
Give me a fucking break!
These people are helping us.

287
00:43:35.380 --> 00:43:37.900
You fucking asshole!

288
00:43:40.660 --> 00:43:44.420
You know what Dad
really said before he died?

289
00:43:48.860 --> 00:43:52.580
He told me
to keep you out of the business.

290
00:43:54.020 --> 00:43:56.580
You're such a fucking liar.

291
00:43:56.660 --> 00:44:00.580
Because you couldn't do what I do.
you're too fucking weak!

292
00:44:34.500 --> 00:44:36.420
Omar?

293
00:44:50.780 --> 00:44:54.580
The city is under guard.
the police is everywhere.

294
00:44:54.660 --> 00:44:57.940
- How do we get out of here?
- I know a back route out of the city.

295
00:44:58.020 --> 00:45:00.500
Then we take the trucks
from Mali to Tangiers.

296
00:45:00.580 --> 00:45:05.380
You can find a new ship there.
so we won't waste too much time.

297
00:45:05.460 --> 00:45:09.420
Could we go to Casablanca?
'Cause I have a contact there.

298
00:45:09.500 --> 00:45:12.860
I can make it work.
These are my best men.

299
00:45:12.940 --> 00:45:14.940
Hi.

300
00:45:15.500 --> 00:45:17.620
Come on.

301
00:45:22.500 --> 00:45:24.500
We gotta go.

302
00:46:11.140 --> 00:46:14.740
When did it start?

303
00:46:20.940 --> 00:46:23.940
Chris? When did it start?

304
00:46:33.700 --> 00:46:36.260
When did the spasms start?

305
00:46:44.500 --> 00:46:47.860
I don't know
what you're talking about.
